.SH "Member Function Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "drawArc (\fBPoint\fP center, number float xRadius, number float yRadius, number float startAngle, number float endAngle, \fBAttributes\fP attrs)"

.PP
Draw an elliptical arc using the specified center, radii, and angle range\&. This function draws an elliptical arc (a portion of an ellipse) using the specified center point, radii, and angle range\&. The arc is drawn with the given attributes for styling\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIcenter\fP The center point of the ellipse in screen coordinates 
.br
\fIxRadius\fP The horizontal radius of the ellipse in pixels 
.br
\fIyRadius\fP The vertical radius of the ellipse in pixels 
.br
\fIstartAngle\fP The starting angle of the arc in radians (0 = 12 o'clock position, positive = clockwise) 
.br
\fIendAngle\fP The ending angle of the arc in radians 
.br
\fIattrs\fP The \fBAttributes\fP object containing styling information (line color, thickness, fill, etc\&.)
.RE
.PP
The arc is drawn as a portion of an ellipse defined by the center point and radii\&. The angle parameters specify which portion of the ellipse to draw, starting from startAngle and ending at endAngle\&.

.PP
Angles are measured in radians, with 0 radians pointing up (12 o'clock position)\&. Positive angles go clockwise, negative angles go counter-clockwise\&.

.PP
\fBWarning\fP
.RS 4
If startAngle equals endAngle, no arc will be drawn 
.RE
.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
The arc is drawn using the current transformation matrix and clipping region
.RE
.PP
