.SS "drawSphere (\fBPoint\fP center, number float radius, \fBAttributes\fP attrs)"

.PP
Draws a textured sphere at the specified center point with given radius and styling attributes\&. This function renders a 3D sphere with a texture applied from a single \fBImage\fP\&. The sphere is drawn using perspective projection and includes lighting calculations for realistic 3D appearance\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIcenter\fP The center point of the sphere in screen coordinates 
.br
\fIradius\fP The radius of the sphere in pixels 
.br
\fIattrs\fP The attributes to use to draw the sphere
.RE
.PP
\fBAttributes\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
texture() The \fBImage\fP containing the texture to apply to the sphere
.IP "\(bu" 2
sphereRotation() The rotation angle of the sphere around its vertical axis in radians
.IP "\(bu" 2
polarOffset() The offset for the polar coordinates (latitude/longitude mapping) in radians
.IP "\(bu" 2
lightOffset() The offset for the lighting calculation in radians
.PP

.PP
The function creates a 3D sphere by mapping the 2D texture from the \fBImage\fP provided by attrs\&.texture onto a spherical surface\&. The texture is wrapped around the sphere using spherical coordinates, offset by attrs\&.sphereRotation, with the rotation happening around the pole define at attrs\&.polarOffset\&.

.PP
The lighting calculation uses the attrs\&.lightOffset parameter to determine how light falls on the sphere, creating a realistic 3D appearance with highlights and shadows\&.

.PP
\fBWarning\fP
.RS 4
Very large texture (image) or radius values may impact rendering performance
.RE
